# Act Configuration for Local Workflow Testing
# This file configures the `act` tool to run GitHub Actions locally
# Format: One flag per line, no special quoting

# Use default Ubuntu image (lightweight; gitea runs as sibling service, not DinD)
# Jobs connect to gitea service via Docker network at http://gitea:3000
-P ubuntu-latest=ghcr.io/catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest

# Set working directory (default is current directory)
# -C /path/to/repo

# Default: Run all jobs from specified workflow
# Override with: act --job <job-name> to run a specific job
# Example: act --file .github/workflows/test-harness.yml -j test-release
